text: [Music]
the core concept of a classical computer
is a bit which can be 0 or 1 and all the
processing in those bits and all the
logic and all the algorithms are based
on zeros or ones all the characters and
all the flow is based on 0 and 1 and at
a quantum computer that is not the case
because the qubit which is what you can
call the equivalent of a bit in a
quantum computer can be 0
it can also be 1 but it can also be a
combination of 0 and 1 and that is of
course entirely different from a
traditional computer and while that may
sound strange it actually is not strange
because nature is all about quantum
mechanics and the computers that we have
today or pretty artificial because we
exclude the what we call the
superposition we say that every bit
should be 0 or 1 but that's not how
nature works there are states that are a
combination of zeros and ones so a
quantum computer is much much closer to
two real nature than a classical
computer
